<h2>Customization</h2>
All folding windows are completely custom to your particular job. As a result, the number of panels, the direction of the panels, and dimensions of the unit and panels are all cut to your measurements. Therefore you can add wood veneer to the frame to mimic the look of a true wooden window as well as other decorative options. Eight standard finishes are available along with any custom color your job may require. Also, corrosion resistant anodized options are available. There are two frame types available: thermal and non-thermal. Utilize non-thermal frames in interior applications and where the windows do not come in contact with rain or the wind.

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37024" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/folding-glass-windows-conewago-inn.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Grid Profiles</h2>
Customers choose from several different grid profiles including a square, Ogee, and traditional shape. The gridwork can match the frame finish or be a different color which adds visual appeal. Stained glass, art glass, etched glass, and any other decorative glass can be utilized in the folding windows.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-37025" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/fgwindows-commericla.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Installation</h2>
